Definition:
• static organization of the software’s code artifacts: packages,
modules, and binaries
Purpose:
• structuring of the system in the development environment
• organization of source code > runtime structure
Other core elements:
• Subsystems
• Libraries
• Build components
Relationships:
• mapping between elements in the Logical View and the actual code
artifacts that implement them
Main concerns:
• Reuse
• Portability
• Build management
Target audience:
• Developers (particularly those involved in implementation, integration, and
build processes)